		<title type="html"><![CDATA[Yet Another Sandboxie Portable]]></title>

		
		<content type="html" xml:base="https://forums.sandboxie.com/phpBB3/viewtopic.php?t=12014&amp;p=75060#p75060"><![CDATA[
Hi All!<br><br>Just want to share my own way to make sandboxie portable.<br><br>This version supports plugins and settings storing from one run to another as well as configuring Sandbox folder place.<br><br><a href="http://tools.safezone.cc/gjf/Sandboxie-portable.zip" class="postlink">So here it is</a>.<br><br>To start Sandboxie simply run start.cmd. No need to reboot after that. When your work is done please run stop.cmd - in this case all services will be stooped, but driver will remains in memory until next reboot (so please keep it in mind).<br><br>All initial settings are stored in Sandboxie.ini.template file. Please look thru it. As you can see it is simple sandboxie.ini file but with possibility to include in the path $(InstallDrive) template which means the drive where start.cmd started. Syou can simply change paths in the way you see fit including plugin paths, sandbox paths etc.<br><br>If you will change something during your work Sandboxie.ini.template will be updated in according to your changes.<br><br>It would be good to see some comments / suggestions here.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="https://forums.sandboxie.com/phpBB3/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=3972">gjf</a> — Mon Dec 05, 2011 10:48 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
